last_release_prior_v2_11_1: 2026-06-13 v2.11.1 (PR #37 feature→dev merge 144324e, PR #38 dev→main merge c0b2343; release https://github.com/Data-Wise/rforge/releases/tag/v2.11.1; CI green on main RForge CI + Deploy Documentation; tap PR Data-Wise/homebrew-tap#123 MERGED — formula+manifest → v2.11.1, sha256 0a5538ba…, desc unchanged 41, ruby -c OK, --diff only pre-existing bin.mkpath drift). Patch (41 commands, no surface change): closes the s7-review runtime family deferred in v2.11.0 — `method_on_missing_class` (a method whose dispatch class has no resolvable namespace binding = unreachable method). Refuted the "not decidable from registry alone" deferral: S7_method carries @signature (dispatch class objects); resolution by OBJECT IDENTITY (not @name — review caught a binding≠@name FP on Foo<-new_class("Bar")); structured {generic,class} output. Built TDD-first (autonomous, pre-approved) from SPEC-s7-method-missing-class-2026-06-13.md; focused adversarial review caught 1 BLOCKER + 2 MINORs (all fixed, re-verified vs real R). pytest 349, test-all 41/41.
