in_progress_prior: 2026-06-13 v2.10.0 — review-hardened. Adversarial review of the bundle (5 dims, 2-lens verify) before release caught 3 real bug-classes the TDD gates missed, all FIXED via PR #33 (merge d7bd31b): (1) BLOCKER diff-aware --changed silent false-negative — _run_check_at ignored its ref (HEAD vs HEAD) so r:check --changed reported ok with real ERRORs; now honest scope-only, tagging deferred, real-git e2e test replaces the mocked one that hid it; (2) deps_sync _apply_patch dropped version constraints on --write (corrupted DESCRIPTION; affected r:use-package AND r:deps-sync since v2.5.0) — now preserves verbatim specs; (3) s7review 4 false positives (no comment/string masking; new_property flagged as type) — added masking seam. pytest 290→298; test-all 41/41. Lesson saved [[feedback_adversarial_review_prose_contracts]]. ---- Bundle (PR #32, merge 85881e8): #26 r:s7-review (+1) + scaffolding r:use-* (+3) + diff-aware --changed (+0). #26 r:s7-review (lib/s7review.py, cranlint archetype, 5 advisory families; --eco/R-pass deferred; +1) + scaffolding r:use-test/use-package/use-vignette (lib/scaffold.py+usethis_infra.py, dry-run default + --write, reuses deps_sync._apply_patch/scan_usage; +3) + diff-aware --changed (lib/changed.py, flags on r:check/test/lint, merge-base 2nd-check deferred; +0). 35→39 commands; test-all 36→41; pytest 232→290. Built by 3 sequential implementer agents + a docs gap-pass agent in one bundle worktree; mkdocs --strict clean. Specs+plans in docs/specs/. NEXT: dev→main release PR + tap sync (or bundle more first).
