decisions:
  - date: 2026-05-10
    decision: "MCP is now optional (Path A → B)"
    rationale: |
      User goal: maintain only rforge (not also rforge-mcp). Half of MCP's
      13 tools were placeholders; user is single-client (Claude Code, no
      Desktop/Cursor); plugin commands are markdown prompts that work via
      Claude Code's built-in tools without an MCP server.
    path_a_shipped:
      commit: <next>
      changes:
        - "package.json: drop peerDependencies.rforge-mcp"
        - "README.md: reframe Part 1 (MCP install) as optional"
        - "tests/test-plugin-structure.sh: remove Test 8 (peer-dep assertion)"
        - "CHANGELOG.md: document the decoupling in v1.2.0 entry"
    path_b_spec:
      file: docs/specs/SPEC-mcp-absorb-2026-05-10.md
      summary: |
        Migration plan for absorbing rforge-mcp's 7 implemented tools into
        rforge's lib/. 4 phases. Drops 6 placeholder MCP tools entirely.
        Estimated 3-4 sessions, not urgent — A already unblocks npm install.

## 🎯 Next Action

✅ **v2.15.0 RELEASED (2026-06-21) — no active task.** dev ≡ main @ v2.15.0 (PR #51 dev→main merge 58620b9; [release](https://github.com/Data-Wise/rforge/releases/tag/v2.15.0); CI green on main; tap PR #129 MERGED → formula+manifest v2.15.0, sha256 d2661fa4…; brew upgrade + audit + test pass, installed plugin.json 2.15.0). `lib/rcmd.py` code-review remediation (P1–P4): `--platforms` allow-list validation (`lib/rhub.py`), bounded Rscript timeouts, `s7runtime` R extracted to `lib/r/s7runtime.R`, `rcmd.py` split into `lib/rsnippets.py` + `lib/rhub.py`. No surface change (41 commands); CLI byte-identical. pytest 470, test-all 44/44. Built TDD-first; hardened by a dynamic multi-agent adversarial-verify workflow that caught 2 P1 regressions (allow-list too narrow; `ubuntu-gcc` typo) the green gates missed.

✅ **v2.14.0 RELEASED (2026-06-20)** — 8 CRAN gap-fill checks (PR #47, G1–G8) + `r:rhub` overhaul (PR #48); PR #49 dev→main; CI green; tap PR synced to v2.14.0. 41 commands.

Open candidates (all low-priority):

A) ✅ **diff-aware baseline caching — SHIPPED v2.13.0 (PR #43→dev, #45→main).** Per-package baseline cache under `~/.rforge/baseline-cache/` keyed by `(repo, merge-base SHA, kind, package, flags)`; a growing changed-set reuses already-baselined packages, re-runs only uncached ones; self-invalidating; LRU-20; `--no-cache` + `lib.changed --clear-cache`. New surface: `r:check`/`r:test`/`r:lint --no-cache` (+1 flag each, no new command). Closes the last v2.11.0 `--changed` follow-up. Spec: `SPEC-diff-aware-baseline-caching-2026-06-13.md`.
B) 🟢 **s7-review breadth** — two independent sub-items. (1) **cross-package S7 *contract* checks** — ✅ **SPECCED** (`SPEC-s7-cross-package-contracts-2026-06-13.md`, approved design: static `--eco` extension; v1 = `cross_package_undeclared_contract` + `cross_package_unexported_class`, contract-drift deferred; the static ecosystem sibling of v2.12.0 `method_undeclared_dependency`). ✅ **SHIPPED v2.13.0 (PR #44→dev, #45→main)** — the `cross-package-contract` family in `--eco`. (2) **full R6/S4 *convention* checking** — ⏸️ **PARKED** (decision 2026-06-13): low ecosystem value — rforge is S7-focused, `check_legacy_oop` (v2.10.0) already gives the migration-leftover signal (`legacy_s4_in_s7`/`legacy_r5_in_s7`/`legacy_s3_generic` when co-residing with `new_class`), and full R6/S4 convention linting overlaps lintr. Revisit only if a concrete need appears; would need its own spec. (`method_undeclared_dependency` shipped v2.12.0.)
C) ✅ **Index redesign (A+)** — SHIPPED (PR #42 dev→main, docs-only, live-verified): grid cards + "Where rforge fits" mermaid lifecycle + collapsed the 13 "What's new" sections to one `{{ rforge.version }}`-macro'd section. `PROPOSAL-index-redesign-2026-06-13.md` (kept for provenance).

